Note:
Runa Standard Library: Code Generation

Production-grade code generation system for programmatic creation of
source code, templates, and dynamic compilation capabilities.

Features:
- Template-based code generation with variable substitution
- Dynamic code construction from ASTs
- Multi-target output (Runa, Python, JavaScript, etc.)
- Code formatting and beautification
- Variable scoping and context management
- Integration with AST manipulation for complete metaprogramming
:End Note

Import "metaprogramming/ast_manipulation" as AST

Note: Code generation types and configuration
Type called "CodeTemplate":
    name as String
    template_text as String
    variables as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CodeGenerator":
    target_language as String
    indent_size as Integer
    line_ending as String
    context as Dictionary[String, Any]
    templates as Dictionary[String, CodeTemplate]

Type OutputFormat is:
    | Runa
    | Python
    | JavaScript
    | TypeScript
    | Go
    | Rust

Type called "GenerationContext":
    variables as Dictionary[String, Any]
    scopes as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    current_indent as Integer
    output_buffer as List[String]

Note: Template creation and management
Process called "create_template" that takes name as String and template_text as String returns CodeTemplate:
    Let variables be extract_template_variables with text as template_text
    Return CodeTemplate with:
    name as name
    template_text as template_text
    variables as variables
    metadata as dictionary

Process called "extract_template_variables" that takes text as String returns List[String]:
    Let variables be list
    Let i be 0
    Let text_length be String.length with str as text While i is less than text_length:
    If String.char_at with str as text and index as i is equal to "$" and i 1 is less than text_length and String.char_at with str as text and index as i 1 is equal to "{":
    Set i to i 2
    Let var_start be i
    While i is less than text_length and String.char_at with str as text and index as i is not equal to "}":
    Set i to i 1
    If i is less than text_length:
    Let var_name be String.substring with str as text and start as var_start and end as i
    If var_name is not in variables:
    Add var_name to variables
    Set i to i 1 Return variables

Process called "register_template" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and template as CodeTemplate:
    Set generator.templates[template.name] to template

Process called "get_template" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and name as String returns Optional[CodeTemplate]:
    If name is in generator.templates:
    Return Some(generator.templates[name])
    Return None

Note: Code generator creation and configuration
Process called "create_generator" that takes target as OutputFormat returns CodeGenerator:
    Let target_string be format_to_string with format as target
    Let indent_size be get_default_indent with target as target
    Let line_ending be get_default_line_ending with target as target Return CodeGenerator with:
    target_language as target_string
    indent_size as indent_size
    line_ending as line_ending
    context as dictionary
    templates as dictionary

Process called "format_to_string" that takes format as OutputFormat returns String:
    Match format:
    When Runa:
    Return "runa"
    When Python:
    Return "python"
    When JavaScript:
    Return "javascript"
    When TypeScript:
    Return "typescript"
    When Go:
    Return "go"
    When Rust:
    Return "rust"

Process called "get_default_indent" that takes target as OutputFormat returns Integer:
    Match target:
    When Python:
    Return 4
    When Go:
    Return 1 Note: Uses tabs
    When Rust:
    Return 4
    Otherwise:
    Return 2

Process called "get_default_line_ending" that takes target as OutputFormat returns String:
    Return "\n" Note: Unix-style line endings

Note: Context and variable management
Process called "create_context" returns GenerationContext:
    Return GenerationContext with:
    variables as dictionary
    scopes as list containing dictionary
    current_indent as 0
    output_buffer as list

Process called "push_scope" that takes context as GenerationContext:
    Add dictionary to context.scopes

Process called "pop_scope" that takes context as GenerationContext:
    If List.length with lst as context.scopes is greater than 1:
    List.pop with lst as context.scopes

Process called "set_variable" that takes context as GenerationContext and name as String and value as Any:
    Let current_scope be List.last with lst as context.scopes
    Set current_scope[name] to value

Process called "get_variable" that takes context as GenerationContext and name as String returns Optional[Any]:
    For i from List.length with lst as context.scopes - 1 down to 0:
    Let scope be List.get with lst as context.scopes and index as i
    If name is in scope:
    Return Some(scope[name]) If name is in context.variables:
    Return Some(context.variables[name]) Return None

Note: Template rendering and substitution
Process called "render_template" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and template_name as String and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Let template_opt be get_template with generator as generator and name as template_name
    If template_opt is None:
    Throw "Template not found: " followed by template_name Let template be template_opt as CodeTemplate
    Return substitute_variables with text as template.template_text and context as context

Process called "substitute_variables" that takes text as String and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Let result be ""
    Let i be 0
    Let text_length be String.length with str as text While i is less than text_length:
    If String.char_at with str as text and index as i is equal to "$" and i 1 is less than text_length and String.char_at with str as text and index as i 1 is equal to "{":
    Set i to i 2
    Let var_start be i
    While i is less than text_length and String.char_at with str as text and index as i is not equal to "}":
    Set i to i 1
    If i is less than text_length:
    Let var_name be String.substring with str as text and start as var_start and end as i
    Let var_value be get_variable with context as context and name as var_name
    If var_value is not None:
    Set result to result followed by String.from with value as var_value
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result followed by "${" followed by var_name followed by "}"
    Set i to i 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result followed by String.char_at with str as text and index as i
    Set i to i 1 Return result

Process called "render_with_variables" that takes template_text as String and variables as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Let context be create_context()
    For each name and value in variables:
    set_variable with context as context and name as name and value as value Return substitute_variables with text as template_text and context as context

Note: AST to code generation
Process called "ast_to_code" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator returns String:
    Let context be create_context()
    Return generate_from_ast with node as node and generator as generator and context as context

Process called "generate_from_ast" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Match node.node_type:
    When "Literal":
    Return generate_literal with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    When "Identifier":
    Return generate_identifier with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    When "Expression":
    Return generate_expression with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    When "Statement":
    Return generate_statement with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    When "Declaration":
    Return generate_declaration with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    When "Block":
    Return generate_block with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    When "Program":
    Return generate_program with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    Otherwise:
    Return "/* Unknown node type: " followed by node.node_type followed by " */"

Process called "generate_literal" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Return String.from with value as node.value

Process called "generate_identifier" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Return node.value as String

Process called "generate_expression" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Let parts be list
    For each child in node.children:
    Add generate_from_ast with node as child and generator as generator and context as context to parts
    Return String.join with parts as parts and separator as " "

Process called "generate_statement" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Let stmt_code be generate_expression with node as node and generator as generator and context as context
    Return get_indent with context as context followed by stmt_code followed by get_statement_terminator with generator as generator

Process called "generate_declaration" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Return generate_statement with node as node and generator as generator and context as context

Process called "generate_block" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    increase_indent with context as context
    Let block_lines be list For each child in node.children:
    Add generate_from_ast with node as child and generator as generator and context as context to block_lines decrease_indent with context as context
    Return String.join with parts as block_lines and separator as generator.line_ending

Process called "generate_program" that takes node as AST.ASTNode and generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Let program_lines be list For each child in node.children:
    Add generate_from_ast with node as child and generator as generator and context as context to program_lines Return String.join with parts as program_lines and separator as generator.line_ending

Note: Formatting and indentation utilities
Process called "get_indent" that takes context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Let indent_string be ""
    For i from 0 to context.current_indent - 1:
    Set indent_string to indent_string followed by " "
    Return indent_string

Process called "increase_indent" that takes context as GenerationContext:
    Set context.current_indent to context.current_indent 1

Process called "decrease_indent" that takes context as GenerationContext:
    If context.current_indent is greater than 0:
    Set context.current_indent to context.current_indent - 1

Process called "get_statement_terminator" that takes generator as CodeGenerator returns String:
    Match generator.target_language:
    When "python":
    Return ""
    When "go":
    Return ""
    Otherwise:
    Return ";"

Note: Code building and output
Process called "build_code" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and context as GenerationContext returns String:
    Return String.join with parts as context.output_buffer and separator as generator.line_ending

Process called "emit_line" that takes context as GenerationContext and line as String:
    Add line to context.output_buffer

Process called "emit_indented_line" that takes context as GenerationContext and line as String:
    Add get_indent with context as context followed by line to context.output_buffer

Process called "emit_block_start" that takes context as GenerationContext and line as String:
    emit_indented_line with context as context and line as line
    increase_indent with context as context

Process called "emit_block_end" that takes context as GenerationContext and line as String:
    decrease_indent with context as context
    emit_indented_line with context as context and line as line

Note: Built-in templates for common patterns
Process called "setup_builtin_templates" that takes generator as CodeGenerator:
    Let function_template be create_template with name as "function" and template_text as "Process called \"${name}\" that takes ${params} returns ${return_type}:\n ${body}"
    register_template with generator as generator and template as function_template Let class_template be create_template with name as "type" and template_text as "Type called \"${name}\":\n${fields}"
    register_template with generator as generator and template as class_template Let import_template be create_template with name as "import" and template_text as "Import \"${module}\" as ${alias}"
    register_template with generator as generator and template as import_template

Process called "generate_function" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and name as String and params as String and return_type as String and body as String returns String:
    Let context be create_context()
    set_variable with context as context and name as "name" and value as name
    set_variable with context as context and name as "params" and value as params
    set_variable with context as context and name as "return_type" and value as return_type
    set_variable with context as context and name as "body" and value as body Return render_template with generator as generator and template_name as "function" and context as context

Process called "generate_type" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and name as String and fields as String returns String:
    Let context be create_context()
    set_variable with context as context and name as "name" and value as name
    set_variable with context as context and name as "fields" and value as fields Return render_template with generator as generator and template_name as "type" and context as context

Process called "generate_import" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and module as String and alias as String returns String:
    Let context be create_context()
    set_variable with context as context and name as "module" and value as module
    set_variable with context as context and name as "alias" and value as alias Return render_template with generator as generator and template_name as "import" and context as context

Note: Validation and formatting
Process called "validate_generated_code" that takes code as String and target as OutputFormat returns Boolean:
    Note: Basic validation - could be extended with actual parsing
    If String.length with str as code is equal to 0:
    Return false Note: Check for basic syntax requirements based on target
    Match target:
    When Python:
    Return validate_python_syntax with code as code
    When JavaScript:
    Return validate_javascript_syntax with code as code
    When Runa:
    Return validate_runa_syntax with code as code
    Otherwise:
    Return true

Process called "validate_runa_syntax" that takes code as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Basic Runa syntax validation
    Return not String.contains with str as code and substring as "//" and not String.contains with str as code and substring as "/* "

Process called "validate_python_syntax" that takes code as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Basic Python syntax validation checking balanced brackets and indentation
    Let bracket_count be 0
    Let paren_count be 0
    Let brace_count be 0 For each char in code:
    If char is equal to "[":
    Set bracket_count to bracket_count 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "]":
    Set bracket_count to bracket_count - 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "(":
    Set paren_count to paren_count 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to ")":
    Set paren_count to paren_count - 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "{":
    Set brace_count to brace_count 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "}":
    Set brace_count to brace_count - 1 Return bracket_count is equal to 0 and paren_count is equal to 0 and brace_count is equal to 0

Process called "validate_javascript_syntax" that takes code as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Basic JavaScript syntax validation checking balanced brackets and semicolons
    Let bracket_count be 0
    Let paren_count be 0
    Let brace_count be 0 For each char in code:
    If char is equal to "[":
    Set bracket_count to bracket_count 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "]":
    Set bracket_count to bracket_count - 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "(":
    Set paren_count to paren_count 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to ")":
    Set paren_count to paren_count - 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "{":
    Set brace_count to brace_count 1
    Otherwise if char is equal to "}":
    Set brace_count to brace_count - 1 Return bracket_count is equal to 0 and paren_count is equal to 0 and brace_count is equal to 0

Process called "format_code" that takes code as String and target as OutputFormat returns String:
    Note: Apply target-specific formatting rules
    Let lines be String.split with str as code and separator as "\n"
    Let formatted_lines be list For each line in lines:
    Add String.trim with str as line to formatted_lines Return String.join with parts as formatted_lines and separator as "\n"